reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Gold Plated, Four solid capacitors
reviews.reviewText: It's a good product that has four (270 FP 16 V) solid capacitors. The best part is the PCI-E link head, and the PCI Express slot is gold-plated, which is more conductive, more resistant, and stable. It works perfectly with my setup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Functions Well, works as advertised
reviews.reviewText: Purchased this riser for a small mining rig, specifically outfitted onto a 3070. I understand that some cheaper risers have had instances of burning, it hasn’t happened yet. The board is sturdy with very little flex and can maintain the weight of the GPU without difficulty, although I wouldn’t recommend holding it up for long periods of time without stabilizing the GPU. In general with all risers, I would strongly suggest that you avoid using the SATA to 6 pin adapter and use a 6 pin pcie adapter to power the board - SATA power can often be risky to both the card and board.
